<?xml-stylesheet type="text/xsl" href="assets/xml/rss.xsl" media="all"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>A quality noob blog</title><link>https://alhern.github.io/</link><description>Et élucubrations diverses.</description><atom:link href="https://alhern.github.io/rss.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"></atom:link><language>en</language><copyright>Contents © 2018 &lt;a href="mailto:audev@protonmail.com"&gt;Alhern&lt;/a&gt; </copyright><lastBuildDate>Sat, 17 Mar 2018 17:25:35 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>Nikola (getnikola.com)</generator><docs>http://blogs.law.harvard.edu/tech/rss</docs><item><title>Noob notes for PR</title><link>https://alhern.github.io/posts/noob%2Bnotes%2Bfor%2Bpr/</link><dc:creator>Alhern</dc:creator><description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;A simple reminder for PRs:
1. Fork.
2. Clone.
3. &lt;tt class="docutils literal"&gt;git check out &lt;span class="pre"&gt;-b&lt;/span&gt; [somefeature]&lt;/tt&gt;
4. Edit the code.
5. &lt;tt class="docutils literal"&gt;git commit &lt;span class="pre"&gt;-a&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="pre"&gt;-m&lt;/span&gt; [commitmessage]&lt;/tt&gt;
6. &lt;tt class="docutils literal"&gt;git push &lt;span class="pre"&gt;--set-upstream&lt;/span&gt; origin [somefeature]&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Et voilà.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description><category>github</category><category>pr</category><guid>https://alhern.github.io/posts/noob%2Bnotes%2Bfor%2Bpr/</guid><pubDate>Thu, 29 Jun 2017 20:02:57 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title>Mongoose + Heroku + mLab</title><link>https://alhern.github.io/posts/mongoose-%2B-heroku-%2B-mlab/</link><dc:creator>Alhern</dc:creator><description>&lt;ol class="arabic"&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;p class="first"&gt;Configurate Heroku with:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre class="literal-block"&gt;
heroku config:set MONGOLAB_URI=mongodb://[username]:[password]@xx000000.mlab.com:00000/[project-name]
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;p class="first"&gt;Add to app.js:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre class="literal-block"&gt;
const mongodbUri = process.env.MONGOLAB_URI;

mongoose.connect(mongodbUri, (err, res) =&amp;gt; {
    if (err) {
        console.log(err);
    } else {
        console.log('success!!!!!!!!!');
    }
});
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;p class="first"&gt;At the bottom:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre class="literal-block"&gt;
const port = process.env.PORT

app.listen(process.env.PORT);
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;</description><category>heroku</category><category>mlab</category><category>mongoose</category><guid>https://alhern.github.io/posts/mongoose-%2B-heroku-%2B-mlab/</guid><pubDate>Tue, 27 Jun 2017 22:57:17 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title>Remembering Mongo</title><link>https://alhern.github.io/posts/remembering-mongo/</link><dc:creator>Alhern</dc:creator><description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Just the basics so I don't have to scratch my noob head every time I start reworking on Mongo months later.
Here's for Windows.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;First:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre class="literal-block"&gt;
C:\Program Files\MongoDB\Server\3.4\bin\mongod.exe --dbpath /Users\[name]\mongo-data
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Then simply:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre class="literal-block"&gt;
C:\Program Files\MongoDB\Server\3.4\bin\mongo.exe
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description><category>mongo</category><guid>https://alhern.github.io/posts/remembering-mongo/</guid><pubDate>Wed, 14 Jun 2017 14:15:08 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title>Welcome to Nikola</title><link>https://alhern.github.io/posts/welcome-to-nikola/</link><dc:creator>Roberto Alsina</dc:creator><description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;div class="figure"&gt;
